article.headline: Morehead St. 82, Tennessee Tech 71
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Senior forward Quentin Pryor scored 20 points to lead Morehead State to a 82-71 win Saturday over Tennessee Tech. Tennessee Tech (6-9, 2-4 Ohio Valley Conference) led for the most part of the first half, but Francis Kabore's shot with 8:06 left pushed the Golden Eagles ahead 26-18. Morehead State reeled off 11 of the next 13 points and took a 29-28 advantage on a Pryor 3-pointer with 3:54 left. The Eagles led 35-33 at the half. Morehead State (9-5, 5-1) never lost the lead in the second half. Tech got to within 37-36 early in the second half, but the Golden Eagles pushed their lead into double figures. A pair of free throws by Nikola Stojakovic, who finished with a game high 11 assists, with 4:43 left put the Eagles ahead by its biggest margin, 71-57. Besides Pryor, Shaun Williams finished in double figures with 18 points. Tennessee Tech was led by Anthony Fisher's 25 points while Belton Rivers finished with 18.
